The paper proposes a framework for speeding up several machine learning algorithms with almost no loss of accuracy using structured matrices. The paper discusses applications including kernel approximations, dimensionality reduction, LSH techniques, deep learning, convex optimization, and quantization. These applications are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.IT, and cs.NE.
